  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PARC - Water, food and NFI distribution</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PARC will be providing food packages and access to clean drinking water for displaced families affected by recent violence across Gaza.
1) Distribution of 3000 cubic metres of water at 100 distribution points (including 83 UNRWA and 12 public shelters), 100,000 people will be provided with 5 litres for 6 days with ERF OCHA funds providing the additional 10 Ltrs per person per day for that period to meet SPhere standards. 
2) Distribution of food/NFI packages (containing canned tomatoes, oil, rice, lentils, beans, sugar, salt, milk for children, sanitary pads, nappies) with supply of food for 3 days for 1,080 familes (8,640 people) across Gaza&apos;s 5 governorates: North Gaza (Ezbit Abed Rabu); Gaza City (Alshijaeyia); Deir Alballah (Alfurat camp, Alnisarat); Khan Younis (Alasharqiya, Abasan, Khuzaa); Rafah (Alshoka, Umm Alnour, Altanour, Khirbit Aladas). Significant coordination and follow up with the UN clusters and other agencies to ensure continued support to beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will bring about significant change to the lives of people living in Gaza who have been affected by the recent conflict. Activities have been designed to specifically target people not already served by other agencies, and with full coordination with UNRWA, WASH and Food Security cluste, the Palestinian NGO network and NGOs such as Oxfam and ACF. It will be implemented alongside PARC&apos;s implemenation of the ERF funded by OCHA which PARC have successfully received- this is also for foor and water distribution and is for $247,000.</narrative>
  </description>
